	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hmmm  Ports to Luclin.  This brings up several questions.<BR>
<BR>
1.  How will druid ports work into the entire EQ story line?  Seems like they are forgetting the story line in favor of people complaining it takes to long to get somewhere.<BR>
<BR>
2.  I'm a druid and I don't want ports all over the place.  I enjoy the aspect that several have mentioned about a good run and being in remote places without too many people.  I will however admit that a port to nexus would be nice but as long as its a group port.  Individual ports to these places would be nice just for the convience of travel, but group ports are just going to open the door to the never ending &quot;can you port me?&quot;  Don't get me wrong, I love the extra plat you can make from porting people around, and I refuse to go anon just because I am a druid to avoid these tells.  I'm proud of the fact that I'm a level 40 Druid.  It makes it tough but I am still capable of typing &quot;No, Sorry Busy&quot; every few minutes.  hehe.<BR>
<BR>
3. Why so many at once?  Why not add say 2 to see how it goes?  One to nexus and say one to Katta should be good for starters.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Why not just make the wizard spires clickable or requestable.  The boats keep breaking and the idea of translocators has been meet with approval.  Just change the wizard spire scions translocators.  You say &quot;i wish to journey to luclin&quot; and boom your porting. None of this waiting around for 15 min.  That should cut down alot on the &quot;can you port me's&quot;  and speed up travel to the moon.  Verant seems to be losing its edge of making a game that has a challenge to it, a fantasy world appeal, a all around funtime, at the expense of the bottom dollar because people are complaining they cant make it to level 60 in a week.  Its called EQ for a reason.  Leave the game alone and stop making it easier for the &quot;newbies&quot;.  Make them work as hard as we had to.  They will either leave because they give up to soon, or they will enjoy the &quot;Game&quot; more because they have earned their way up the level ladder. <BR>
<BR>
My vote is leave the ports alone.  It works the way it is, a challenge for all.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
