			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Several Points:<BR>
<BR>
1) RP reason, for those of you who seem so desperately to need one - Relgious-based magic works just fine on Luclin, therefore there is no reason to assume that Tunare or Karana have no sway there.  After all there are both forests and storms on the moon.  Gods live on other PLANES of existence, I hardly think that thy will be hamperded by something as inconsequential as a little vacuum that an upstart mortal wizard can travel through.<BR>
<BR>
2) A lot of us who have been playing this game for a long time are not teenagers and high school students with hours of nothing to do but scarf down pizza and annoy others.  Many, many of us have jobs, families, school, and - dare I say it - lives.  I myself work full-time and go to graduate school, so the practicality of ports around Luclin, reducing travel time and making it easy to get with friends to group is very appealing to me.<BR>
<BR>
3) All of those of you complaining about Druids getting ports to the moon who happen to play on Morell-Thule please e-mail me with your characters names so I can put you on my &quot;not when Cazic bends down and kisses Tunares cheek will I ever ever &quot;port u pls&quot; to anywhere ever again&quot; list.  I get so tickled by all of the druid-bashing that goes on.  If it weren't for the fact that I can't play for ten minutes without getting a tell from someone half way across the globe asking for a port, I might actually take it seriously.  Get a grip people.<BR>
<BR>
Wolfwind Darkenbane - 54 Wanderer Morell-Thule.
				</font>
			</td>

